sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant NOC as NOC Engineer<br/>(CLI / Web UI)
    participant MAIN as main.py<br/>Entry Point
    participant PIPE as ComplianceAuditPipeline
    participant SIM as KamailioSimulator<br/>(Fault Injector)
    participant TWIN as NetworkStateTwin<br/>(IMS Digital Twin)
    participant EVAL as ComplianceEvaluator
    participant FW as Framework Controls<br/>(UK TSA / EU AI Act /<br/>ISO 42001 / NIST / MIT / OECD)
    participant GEMMA as GemmaComplianceAdvisor<br/>(Gemma 4:e4b via Google ADK)
    participant OLLAMA as Ollama Server<br/>(localhost:11434)
    participant OUT as Output<br/>(Files / Web UI)

    Note over NOC,OUT: Phase 1 — Framework & Scenario Selection

    NOC->>MAIN: Select frameworks (e.g. uk_tsa + eu_ai_act)<br/>Select scenario (e.g. pii_sip_header_leak)
    MAIN->>PIPE: run(framework_keys, scenario_key)

    Note over PIPE,SIM: Phase 2 — Compliance Fault Injection

    PIPE->>SIM: inject_compliance_fault(scenario_key)
    SIM->>TWIN: mutate twin state (add alarms, set fault)
    TWIN-->>SIM: updated NetworkStateTwin
    SIM-->>PIPE: (logs[], sip_trace, kamailio_cfg_issue)

    Note right of SIM: Generates realistic Kamailio<br/>log lines and SIP traces<br/>for the compliance violation

    Note over PIPE,FW: Phase 3 — Compliance Evaluation

    PIPE->>EVAL: evaluate(twin, logs, framework_keys)
    loop For each framework
        EVAL->>FW: run control checks (twin, logs)
        FW-->>EVAL: ControlStatus (COMPLIANT / NON_COMPLIANT / PARTIAL)
    end
    EVAL-->>PIPE: AuditReport (findings[], framework_scores{})

    Note right of EVAL: Each control check inspects:<br/>• Twin state (KPIs, config)<br/>• Log patterns (regex)<br/>• Fault scenario metadata

    Note over PIPE,OLLAMA: Phase 4 — AI Reasoning & Remediation (Thinking Mode)

    PIPE->>GEMMA: remediate_finding_async(finding, logs, sip_trace, cfg_issue)
    GEMMA->>GEMMA: Build system prompt with <|think|> prefix
    GEMMA->>OLLAMA: POST /api/generate {model: gemma4:e4b,<br/>prompt: <|think|> + context, stream: true}

    loop Streaming tokens
        OLLAMA-->>GEMMA: token chunks
        GEMMA->>GEMMA: Detect <|channel>thought...  <channel|> blocks
        GEMMA->>GEMMA: Strip thinking block from final answer
    end

    OLLAMA-->>GEMMA: Complete response with thinking + answer
    GEMMA->>GEMMA: _parse_thinking_response(raw)<br/>Extract: thinking_block, final_answer
    GEMMA->>GEMMA: _extract_kamailio_cfg(final_answer)<br/>_extract_remediation_steps(final_answer)
    GEMMA-->>PIPE: GemmaResponse(thinking_block, kamailio_config, steps[])

    Note right of GEMMA: Gemma 4 thinking block:<br/><|channel>thought\n...<channel|><br/>→ stripped before returning<br/>Clean Kamailio cfg returned

    Note over PIPE,OUT: Phase 5 — Auto-Remediation & Verification

    PIPE->>OUT: Save kamailio_{INC}_{control_id}.cfg
    PIPE->>TWIN: update_twin_config (simulate patch applied)
    PIPE->>EVAL: Re-evaluate patched controls
    EVAL-->>PIPE: Updated findings (NON_COMPLIANT → COMPLIANT)

    Note over PIPE,OUT: Phase 6 — Executive Summary & Report

    PIPE->>GEMMA: generate_audit_summary_async(audit_report, logs)
    GEMMA->>OLLAMA: Audit summary prompt (thinking mode)
    OLLAMA-->>GEMMA: Executive summary response
    GEMMA-->>PIPE: GemmaResponse (executive summary)

    PIPE->>OUT: Save compliance_report_{INC}.json
    PIPE-->>NOC: Print compliance verdict<br/>(COMPLIANT / PARTIALLY COMPLIANT / NON-COMPLIANT)

    Note over NOC,OUT: Phase 7 — Web Dashboard (optional)

    NOC->>OUT: Open http://localhost:8001
    OUT->>NOC: Interactive compliance dashboard<br/>(Framework selector, findings table,<br/>AI streaming remediation, charts)
    NOC->>OUT: Click "🤖 Fix" on finding
    OUT->>OLLAMA: Stream Kamailio fix via SSE
    OLLAMA-->>OUT: Streamed tokens
    OUT->>NOC: Real-time Kamailio config display
